---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';
import VideoEmbed from '../../components/VideoEmbed.astro';
import { BUSINESS } from '../../consts';

import residencesHero from '../../assets/residences-hero.jpg';
import residencesSymptoms from '../../assets/residences-symptoms.png';
import residencesFacts from '../../assets/residences-facts.png';
import residencesBenefits from '../../assets/residences-benefits.png';

/*
 * 1:1 reproduction of the live gsuair.com Residences/Home Offices page: same
 * heading, same copy, same order — nothing added, nothing removed. That
 * includes the truncated headline and the editor note at the foot of the page,
 * both kept at the owner's request.
 *
 * The live page's symptom / benefit / facts bullets exist only as flattened
 * images ("boxed bulleted images"), which is what the editor note refers to.
 * They are not text on the live page, so they are not text here — they are
 * reproduced as the same three images, in the same three positions:
 *   - symptoms + facts, side by side after the intro (FEAT_CAT_IMAGE_RND0/1,
 *     CSS background-images on the live page)
 *   - benefits, after the editor note (CONTENT_IMAGE1_RENDERED, a lazy <img>)
 * Their bullet text lives only inside the pixels, so it is transcribed into
 * alt text rather than re-typed as body copy.
 */

// Verbatim from the live page, including the truncated last word.
const heroTitle = 'HOMES CONTAIN DUST, POLLUTANTS, & ALLERGENS. HEALTH IMPACT ON OUR LIVE';
---

<Base
  title="Residences/Home Offices"
  description="Aerus air purifiers for homes and home offices help remove contaminants in the indoor air such as bacteria and pollutants, and reduce the number of allergens in your home."
>
  <PageHero title={heroTitle} image={residencesHero} imageAlt="A street of family homes at sunset">
    <p class="mt-6">
      <a
        href={`tel:${BUSINESS.phoneHref}`}
        class="text-lg font-bold text-white underline underline-offset-4 transition-colors hover:text-accent-400"
      >
        {BUSINESS.phone}
      </a>
    </p>
  </PageHero>

  <!-- Intro -->
  <Section tone="tint">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
        The COVID epidemic, combined with the increase in the amount of time Americans now spend in their homes (90%),
        are the biggest contributing factors to the importance of purifying the indoor air in your home. Along with
        that, 22 million U.S. adults work completely from their homes today. Common sources of indoor air pollution
        include cooking with polluting fuels, smoking, building materials, cleaning products, mold, pet dander, and poor
        ventilation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!--
    Boxed bulleted images, as on the live page (FEAT_CAT_IMAGE_RND0/RND1).
    The live section's <h2> is empty, so there is no heading here either.
  -->
  <Section>
    <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-5xl items-start gap-8 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <Image
        src={residencesSymptoms}
        alt="Symptoms caused by poor indoor air quality: irritation of the eyes, nose, or throat; headaches, dizziness, or fatigue; consistent sneezing from allergens; breathing issues and respiratory diseases; asthma."
        widths={[400, 600, 900]}
        sizes="(min-width: 640px) 24rem, 90vw"
        class="mx-auto w-full rounded-lg shadow-md"
        loading="lazy"
      />
      <Image
        src={residencesFacts}
        alt="Facts: around 3 million deaths per year are attributed to household air pollution; almost half of all pneumonia deaths in children under 5 are linked to household air pollution; poor indoor air quality is linked to respiratory issues like asthma, lung cancer, cardiovascular diseases, and an increased risk of infections, especially in children and the elderly; poor indoor air quality can sometimes be more polluted than outdoor air (due to contaminants in the outdoors have endless space to dissipate; homes do not); indoor concentrations of some pollutants have increased in recent decades due to such factors as energy-efficient building construction, personal care products, pesticides, and household cleaners. References: The World Health Organization; The EPA."
        widths={[400, 600, 864]}
        sizes="(min-width: 640px) 24rem, 90vw"
        class="mx-auto w-full rounded-lg shadow-md"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- East Palestine family story -->
  <Section tone="brand">
    <VideoEmbed
      src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1051369131?h=29bb480f3f"
      title="Beyond Guardian Air - East Palestine family story"
    />
    <p class="mx-auto mt-8 max-w-3xl text-center text-lg leading-relaxed text-brand-100">
      Beyond Guardian Air solves siblings' breathing issues that arose in their home from the disaster in East Palestine
      Ohio. Their mother shares her story.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <!-- Closing copy -->
  <Section tone="tint">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
      <p>
        Aerus Air Purifiers for homes and home offices tremendously help to remove contaminants in the indoor air such
        as bacteria and pollutants. The system also reduces the number of allergens in your home, which is especially
        significant for those with asthma and other breathing issues.
      </p>
      <p>
        Speak with a member of our team today to learn more about our innovative system. We can help you choose the best
        purifier for your home.
      </p>
      <p>I will fix the boxed bulleted images once we decide on final page copy.</p>

      <!--
        Boxed bulleted image, as on the live page (CONTENT_IMAGE1_RENDERED, a
        lazy <img> sitting in this same section, after the editor note).
      -->
      <Image
        src={residencesBenefits}
        alt="Indoor air purification system benefits: works 24/7 in spaces occupied by people and pets; reduces airborne and surface contaminants; eliminates harmful dust, dander, and allergens from your air; purifies surfaces from air-borne contaminants; reduces or eliminates odors; reduces harmful gases; keeps people from recontamination; enhances health and quality of life."
        widths={[400, 600, 864]}
        sizes="(min-width: 640px) 28rem, 90vw"
        class="mx-auto w-full max-w-md rounded-lg shadow-md"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </div>
  </Section>
</Base>
